WEEK 4 : GETTING AND CLEANING DATA

BY KHUSHALI VERMA | IIIT-DELHI

PEER GRADED ASSIGNMENT: COURSE PROJECT

THIS ASSIGNMENT HAS 3 FILES:

1. run_analysis.R
   This R script contains the loading and unzipping of data and further the    following 5 tasks executed on the data set
   
   - Merges the training and the test sets to create one data set.
   - Extracts only the measurements on the mean and standard deviation for each measurement.
   - Uses descriptive activity names to name the activities in the data set
   - Appropriately labels the data set with descriptive variable names.
   - From the data set in step 4, creates a second, independent tidy data set with the average of each variable for each activity and each subject.
   
   
When this script is run, the output in seen in Final Data.txt file.

2. Code_Book
   This contains the definition of all variables, what data they contains and what all changes (transformations) were made to this data to clean it up and complete the tasks.